50|$|Nga thalaut paung (ငါးသလောက်ပေါင်း) is a {{freshwater}} <b>hilsa</b> fish dish from Burmese cuisine. The bony fish {{is cooked}} for hours with soy sauce, vinegar, tomatoes in lemongrass. The preparation melts the bones away.|$|E
50|$|The shads are pelagic (open water) {{schooling}} fish, {{of which}} many are anadromous or even landlocked. Several species are of commercial importance, e.g. in the genus Alosa (river herrings), Brevoortia (menhadens), and <b>Hilsa.</b>|$|E
